## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Blood stasis in the body with wind-dampness obstruction
**Key Symptoms**: Chronic body pain (fixed location), joint stiffness, numbness, heaviness of limbs, worse in damp weather, dark complexion, possibly varicose veins
**Tongue**: Purple or with purple spots
**Pulse**: Wiry and choppy, or deep and choppy

### Secondary Applications
- Chronic arthritis and joint pain
- Fibromyalgia with blood stasis signs
- Chronic low back and leg pain
- Post-injury chronic pain
- Chronic fatigue with body pain
- Peripheral circulation disorders

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Rheumatoid arthritis with blood stasis
- Osteoarthritis with chronic pain
- Fibromyalgia and chronic pain syndromes
- Post-traumatic chronic pain
- Chronic lower back pain
- Peripheral vascular disease

## üìù Therapeutic Actions
**Primary**: Move blood, resolve stasis, expel wind-dampness, stop pain

**Secondary**: Improve circulation, reduce inflammation, strengthen joints, enhance mobility

